			data-trigger-once="gpt:ready"></div>					
					<script type="text/javascript" src="/assets/script/modules/async_gpt.js?v=91"></script>					
	<p>She also underwent another operation to have this implant replaced.</p><p>She said: I did not appeal as I did not have the finances or the legal know-how to do it. When the call came to say they had been granted the permission (to take legal fees from the compensation) there was nothing left.</p><p>Her doctors have advised her that no urgent action needs to be taken about her most recent rupture, which was discovered 11 years after the first, in 2004.</p><p>But the recent story about PIP has left her worried.</p><p>She said: The consultant at the hospital said I need not do anything as it would not harm me. I have spoken to my GP and he also assured me there was nothing to worry about as the substance they are made of is inert. I accepted this as I suffer no effects from it but since the report about PIP implants I cant help but think about it.</p>			<div id="adTag_10" 
			class="ad-gpt adGPTTag hidden-xxs visible-sm MPU" 
			data-adtag-type="MPU" 
			data-size="300x250" 
			data-meta-adtagId="3948/northampton.jp/news" 
			data-adtag-pos="mpu3,artmpu3" 
			data-has-pos="true" 
			data-additional=";weathertoday=heavysnow;weathertomorrow=cloudy" 
			data-nav="news"
			data-pgid="13402290" 
			data-trigger-once="gpt:ready"></div>					
					<script type="text/javascript" src="/assets/script/modules/async_gpt.js?v=91"></script>					
				<div id="adTag_11" 
			class="ad-gpt adGPTTag visible-xxs hidden-sm MPU" 
			data-adtag-type="MPU" 
			data-size="300x250" 
			data-meta-adtagId="3948/northampton.jp/news" 
